'squatting' is an inaccurate term for differentiating telemarking from alpine skiing.  There is MORE 'squatting' in an alpine carve turn.  The difference is the DIRECTION of the balancing foot.  In telemark, the same upper body alignment to the edge as alpine to put pressure on the turning ski, the rear foot slips backwards to allow more force on the front ski, squatting is front/back.  In alpine, the inside ski moves uphill to maintain balance, feet move left/right but still in deeper squat.
